.TH ONELINER "1" "January 2024" "Oneliner v1.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
Oneliner \- Tool to get single line commands.
.SH SYNOPSIS
usage: git [\-f | \fB\-\-file\fR <file_path>] [\-options <value>]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Oneliner is a neat tool that can convert a multiline bash script into a single line command that can be directly run on terminal.
.SH OPTIONS
       Expected value      Description
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR
source path         path to the source file with the code to convert
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR
file path           save the output to file oneliner_out.txt in the given
path (defaults to current working directory)
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-print\fR
on/off              verbose output in CLI
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-multiline\fR 
on/off              output/copy file contents with source formatting
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-copy\fR
on/off              copy the output in clipboard
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
display help and exit
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
show version for Oneliner
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Convert a bash script into single line and get output.
.IP
oneliner -f <path/to/source/file> -p
.TP
Convert a bash script into sinlge line command and save output to a file.
.IP
oneliner -f </path/to/source/file> -o </path/to/out/file>
.SH "REPORTING BUGS"
Report bugs/issues to https://github.com/Surajkumar88/Oneliner/issues

